WEBVTT

00:02.470 --> 00:04.405
**

00:04.438 --> 00:06.674
Good morning.

00:06.707 --> 00:07.775
(CELL PHONE DINGS)

00:07.808 --> 00:09.243
That's your third ding.

00:09.277 --> 00:11.112
Good morning.
It's Carly.

00:11.145 --> 00:14.715
She has arrived
at her pathology conference.

00:14.748 --> 00:15.816
Hmm.

00:15.849 --> 00:17.218
Hmm.

00:19.520 --> 00:22.656
Shaun, you need to
text her back.

00:22.690 --> 00:26.394
Her text wasn't a question.
It doesn't require a response.

00:28.196 --> 00:31.565
True. But it sucks
to be left hanging.

00:32.900 --> 00:34.034
You didn't like
how it felt

00:34.068 --> 00:35.569
when you thought
Carly was ignoring you.

00:42.042 --> 00:45.446
I have received
your message.

00:45.479 --> 00:47.415
(WHOOSH)
Sent.

00:50.718 --> 00:51.785
Hmm.

00:51.819 --> 00:53.354
You made me breakfast?

00:53.387 --> 00:55.823
Oh, God, no.
I ordered breakfast.

00:55.856 --> 00:57.325
But I managed
to keep it warm.

00:58.759 --> 01:01.095
You don't have to do this.
I'm fine.

01:04.398 --> 01:05.399
Did you get any sleep?

01:06.934 --> 01:08.102
I got enough.

01:09.870 --> 01:11.239
Her death's
not your fault.

01:13.107 --> 01:14.475
She knew the risks.

01:14.508 --> 01:17.245
She made a choice
to save her baby.

01:17.278 --> 01:19.713
I bet she'd make
the same choice again,

01:19.747 --> 01:21.382
even knowing
how it would end.

01:23.917 --> 01:25.052
Thank you.

01:25.085 --> 01:27.721
**

01:31.959 --> 01:33.427
Thanks for breakfast.

01:37.398 --> 01:38.932
(SIGHS)

01:42.803 --> 01:45.373
We do a complete
enucleation
of the right eye,

01:45.406 --> 01:47.341
then replace it
with the temporary implant,

01:47.375 --> 01:48.409
and in a few weeks,
you'll...

01:48.442 --> 01:50.211
You know why blind people
don't skydive?

01:52.580 --> 01:54.114
It scares
the hell out of the dog.

01:54.148 --> 01:55.216
(CHUCKLES)

01:56.116 --> 01:57.851
Let the doctors finish.
Okay, bud?

01:57.885 --> 02:00.288
Yeah, cancer eye out.
Fake eye in.

02:00.321 --> 02:01.889
Just like last time.
I got it.

02:05.959 --> 02:06.960
Check it out.

02:08.429 --> 02:09.763
It even moves
and everything.

02:09.797 --> 02:11.131
You can't even tell
it's fake.

02:12.266 --> 02:14.968
Very cool.
Like a bionic superhero.

02:15.002 --> 02:18.539
Yeah, and my superpower
is tripping over stuff.

02:20.441 --> 02:21.942
What time
is the surgery?

02:21.975 --> 02:23.043
3:00.

02:23.076 --> 02:26.079
Which means
I've got six hours left

02:26.113 --> 02:27.948
to blast some aliens.

02:28.982 --> 02:33.053
(LCD SOUNDSYSTEM'S
DANCE YRSELF CLEAN PLAYS)

02:33.086 --> 02:34.322
(VIDEO GAME SOUNDS)

02:34.355 --> 02:37.024
**

02:40.794 --> 02:44.365
* We've got to bring
the resources

02:45.866 --> 02:49.670
* I want to play it
till the time comes

02:50.871 --> 02:52.573
* Oh *

02:52.606 --> 02:55.008
**

02:56.844 --> 02:58.346
If anyone utters the word
"Bubble Girl,"

02:58.379 --> 03:00.314
I will transfer
to a different hospital.

03:00.348 --> 03:02.115
(DR. PARK LAUGHS)

03:09.690 --> 03:11.692
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

03:20.368 --> 03:21.435
APRIL: When you
were his age,

03:21.469 --> 03:25.339
would you have faced
going blind with h-humor,

03:25.373 --> 03:27.475
maturity,
and acceptance?

03:27.508 --> 03:29.209
I would have
burned things down.

03:31.345 --> 03:32.846
He's dealing with it
in his own way.

03:34.248 --> 03:35.383
We'll check in with him

03:35.416 --> 03:37.351
while you're taking care of
the rest of the paperwork.

03:37.385 --> 03:39.219
Make sure Charlie knows
there's people he can talk to.

03:39.253 --> 03:41.722
Thank you.
Thank you.

03:42.890 --> 03:45.293
Dr. Reznick, take
Charlie's blood to the lab.

03:45.326 --> 03:46.560
Dr. Browne,
talk to him.

03:46.594 --> 03:48.228
Maybe he'll open up
to you.

03:48.262 --> 03:51.565
**

03:57.271 --> 03:59.006
(SIGHS, CLEARS THROAT)

04:01.041 --> 04:02.175
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

04:02.209 --> 04:04.845
Heart sounds are normal.
No sign of pericardial
effusion.

04:04.878 --> 04:08.582
SHAUN: You are the oldest
SCID-patient I am aware of.

04:08.616 --> 04:11.018
People with your condition
usually die very young.

04:11.952 --> 04:14.121
Yay. I win.

04:14.154 --> 04:17.425
Tara, imaging confirms
that you have infected
tissue on your right lung,

04:17.458 --> 04:19.360
that's what's causing
your breathing issues.

04:19.393 --> 04:21.995
And we're gonna remove it
with a procedure
called decortication...

04:22.029 --> 04:24.064
And you'll use
the thoracoscopic approach

04:24.097 --> 04:26.099
to decrease
risk of infection.

04:26.133 --> 04:28.436
And I'll be in an enclosed
chamber in the O.R.
What else?

04:28.469 --> 04:32.072
I assure you, we'll be
taking every precaution
to keep you safe.

04:32.105 --> 04:34.742
Dr. Melendez, this building
is a glorified incubator

04:34.775 --> 04:37.010
for every infection
on the planet.

04:37.044 --> 04:38.979
Considering I don't come
with an immune system,

04:39.012 --> 04:40.414
I don't need assurances.

04:40.448 --> 04:42.550
I need you to tell me
how you're gonna not kill me.

04:44.284 --> 04:46.119
SHAUN: We will
administer a course

04:46.153 --> 04:48.255
of broad-spectrum
antibiotics.

04:48.288 --> 04:51.525
You will be transported
to the O.R. under
a respiratory hood.

04:51.559 --> 04:53.561
The room will be equipped
with laminar air flow

04:53.594 --> 04:55.696
and kept at
a positive pressure
of 8 Pascals.

04:55.729 --> 04:57.431
Surgical instruments
will be double-sterilized

04:57.465 --> 04:59.767
and all blood products
will be irradiated.

04:59.800 --> 05:00.901
Thank you, Dr. Murphy.

05:04.405 --> 05:06.974
Visitors will also
have to go through
a strict decontamination...

05:07.007 --> 05:08.776
There won't be any.

05:08.809 --> 05:10.978
The less time I spend
with people, the better.

05:11.011 --> 05:12.245
Are we done?

05:12.279 --> 05:14.448
**

05:15.816 --> 05:17.551
How'd your talk
with Charlie go?

05:17.585 --> 05:19.152
He wants to be
left alone.

05:19.186 --> 05:21.822
No, you want to
be left alone.
And yet here we are.

05:21.855 --> 05:23.657
Precocious pre-teen
going blind.

05:23.691 --> 05:26.994
Come on, that's Claire catnip.
You have to talk to him.

05:27.027 --> 05:29.129
**

05:31.031 --> 05:32.833
Did he have any tests
scheduled?
No.

05:34.368 --> 05:35.969
(SIGHS)

05:36.003 --> 05:37.671
**

05:45.112 --> 05:47.615
No one's seen him,
heard him, smelled him.
I'm calling Security.

05:47.648 --> 05:49.383
Hold on.
What are you doing?

05:50.150 --> 05:51.919
ENNIS: Where's Charlie?

05:51.952 --> 05:53.253
Did something happen?
Is he okay?

05:53.286 --> 05:54.354
He's in imaging.

05:55.856 --> 05:57.925
We'll have him back
very soon.

05:57.958 --> 05:59.793
**

06:01.161 --> 06:02.996
He ordered a ride
15 minutes ago.

06:03.030 --> 06:04.532
To where?
It's close.

06:04.565 --> 06:06.299
We could have him back
before anyone knows he's gone.

06:06.333 --> 06:07.968
Are you insane?
You're right.

06:08.001 --> 06:09.603
It's much better
if we go back in there

06:09.637 --> 06:11.371
and freak out
two already-freaked-out
parents,

06:11.405 --> 06:13.006
and while you're at it,
explain to Andrews

06:13.040 --> 06:14.508
that you didn't do
what he asked you to do.

06:14.542 --> 06:15.809
(SCOFFS)

06:16.644 --> 06:18.211
(SIGHS)

06:20.648 --> 06:22.049
(CELL PHONE DINGS)

06:22.082 --> 06:23.517
Hmm.

06:26.386 --> 06:28.255
**

06:31.892 --> 06:33.060
Which emoji was it?

06:39.933 --> 06:41.201
Just send it to me.

06:43.671 --> 06:45.005
(CELL PHONE DINGS)

06:46.707 --> 06:47.975
Oh...

06:48.008 --> 06:50.310
You told me
I have to respond.

06:50.343 --> 06:53.246
There is no response to...

06:54.848 --> 06:58.652
Okay, I think Carly's
saying she misses you

06:58.686 --> 07:00.488
and wants to know
that you miss her, too.

07:00.521 --> 07:03.390
You know all of that
from one fake face?

07:03.423 --> 07:06.860
Just text her back
something flirty, casual.

07:06.894 --> 07:10.197
Say something like, "I can't
stop thinking about you."

07:10.230 --> 07:13.501
I have stopped thinking
about her many times today.

07:13.534 --> 07:15.168
Do not text Carly that.

07:15.202 --> 07:17.771
(SIGHS)

07:17.805 --> 07:19.406
I have to go.

07:19.439 --> 07:20.741
Okay.

07:23.611 --> 07:25.813
(CROWD CHEERS)

07:29.049 --> 07:30.651
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

07:33.954 --> 07:36.456
(ORGAN PLAYS CHARGE)

07:36.490 --> 07:38.425
This popcorn is terrible.

07:38.458 --> 07:42.195
We have to get you back
before your parents
start to worry.

07:42.229 --> 07:44.397
We're gonna be three years,
five months too late.

07:46.099 --> 07:48.769
The game is a blowout.
So, we leave now...

07:48.802 --> 07:50.103
What's her name?

07:50.137 --> 07:51.338
What?

08:02.149 --> 08:03.817
I dunno.

08:03.851 --> 08:05.953
The only words
I've ever said to her are,

08:05.986 --> 08:07.287
"Can I have a slushy?"

08:08.421 --> 08:11.258
I just wanted to see her
one last time.

08:11.291 --> 08:13.260
Go say hi.
Are you crazy?

08:13.293 --> 08:15.128
I was asking her
that earlier.

08:15.162 --> 08:18.265
Tell her you think
she's the most beautiful girl
you've ever laid eyes on,

08:18.298 --> 08:19.567
and with your last
few hours of sight,

08:19.600 --> 08:21.669
you wanted to
see her face
one more time.

08:21.702 --> 08:23.470
**

08:36.516 --> 08:38.351
As lovely as this is...
Don't ruin the moment.

08:43.356 --> 08:46.526
SHAUN: The necrotic debris
has completely encased
the visceral pleura.

08:46.560 --> 08:48.796
DR. MELENDEZ:
Follow me with the camera.
I don't want to spring a leak.

08:48.829 --> 08:50.130
(MONITOR BEEPING)

08:53.100 --> 08:55.002
Tissue's fused her lungs
to her chest wall.

08:55.035 --> 08:56.336
I need
the Kaiser Forceps.

09:04.244 --> 09:05.312
Damn it.

09:05.345 --> 09:07.214
Tissue's too thick to fit
through the ports.

09:07.247 --> 09:08.949
We need to do
a thoracotomy.

09:08.982 --> 09:10.818
And we can't open her up
in an air-tight chamber.

09:10.851 --> 09:12.052
If we have
to cauterize a bleed,

09:12.085 --> 09:13.186
the whole thing
could explode.

09:15.756 --> 09:18.225
We have to take
our Bubble Girl
out of the bubble.

09:18.258 --> 09:20.928
**

09:28.736 --> 09:31.605
MAN: Lemonade!
Get your ice-cold lemonade!

09:31.639 --> 09:33.641
(ORGAN PLAYING)

09:33.674 --> 09:35.909
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

09:37.778 --> 09:39.546
We've been gone too long.

09:39.579 --> 09:42.382
Calm down. It'll take
the kid 15 seconds
to chicken out.

09:46.854 --> 09:48.255
Or less.
(BAT CRACKS)

09:48.288 --> 09:50.223
(CROWD CHEERING)

09:55.595 --> 09:57.597
I'm a wuss.

09:57.631 --> 10:00.801
Most kids wouldn't
have gone over at all.
Good for you.

10:06.439 --> 10:07.440
Can I...
No.

10:08.642 --> 10:09.777
I'm just...
No.

10:09.810 --> 10:11.712
It better be fast.
What?

10:11.745 --> 10:13.580
We're giving a sad,
nearly blind kid

10:13.613 --> 10:15.048
a few more minutes
in the sun.

10:15.082 --> 10:16.249
We could get
an award for this.

10:16.283 --> 10:18.418
(BAT CRACKS)

10:18.451 --> 10:20.220
(CROWD CHEERING)

10:20.253 --> 10:22.222
(MONITOR BEEPING)

10:22.255 --> 10:24.157
**

10:24.191 --> 10:26.193
DR. MELENDEZ:
Change gloves
every 20 minutes.

10:26.226 --> 10:28.461
We need to be fast,
but extremely careful.

10:30.831 --> 10:31.832
Knife.

10:57.991 --> 11:00.127
It's a Northern
flying squirrel.

11:00.160 --> 11:02.129
They don't fly
so much as glide.

11:02.162 --> 11:03.964
You're lucky
it's not infected.

11:03.997 --> 11:05.966
Well, it's
a fascinating species.

11:05.999 --> 11:08.635
They're uncommonly high-strung
for a nocturnal rodent.

11:10.170 --> 11:11.371
(RUSTLING)

11:12.372 --> 11:13.774
Is the squirrel
in the bag?

11:13.807 --> 11:14.842
Yes.

11:14.875 --> 11:16.810
Henry comes everywhere...
No, no, no, no, no.

11:16.844 --> 11:18.545
That's okay.
I don't need to see him.

11:18.578 --> 11:20.814
(ZIPPER CLOSES)
Okay.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.516
Has he bitten you before?

11:24.885 --> 11:27.220
It was my fault.
I provoke him.

11:28.388 --> 11:29.456
Henry's a good boy.

11:29.489 --> 11:30.590
It's not your fault.

11:30.623 --> 11:31.892
You can't take him
from me.

11:33.794 --> 11:35.328
He's not allowed
to hurt you.

11:35.362 --> 11:37.497
Hi. It's 12:47.

11:37.530 --> 11:38.631
Thank you.

11:38.665 --> 11:40.000
You're 17 minutes late
for your 12:30...

11:40.033 --> 11:42.502
Mrs. Pryce and I
need to have a little talk.

11:42.535 --> 11:44.972
It's okay.
Henry and I
are fine.

11:45.705 --> 11:48.175
**

11:50.844 --> 11:52.379
Who's Henry?

11:52.412 --> 11:53.580
(SIGHS)

11:59.619 --> 12:02.522
You hesitated
before cutting her open.

12:02.555 --> 12:05.325
We had to work fast
once I made the incision.

12:05.358 --> 12:07.094
I was running through
the procedure in my head.

12:08.261 --> 12:10.898
There's no shame in needing
to process a tough loss.

12:12.933 --> 12:14.267
You should talk
to someone.

12:14.301 --> 12:16.870
I'd prefer to focus
on my current patient

12:16.904 --> 12:18.338
rather than
my last one.

12:19.773 --> 12:22.242
**

12:24.611 --> 12:26.746
(RINGING)

12:26.780 --> 12:28.882
CLAIRE: Hey.
Dr. Browne,
where's my patient?

12:28.916 --> 12:29.950
And before you say,
"Imaging,"

12:29.983 --> 12:31.084
I already know
that's not true.

12:31.118 --> 12:33.086
He's with me and Morgan.

12:33.120 --> 12:34.888
He just needed to process
a few things. Everything's...

12:34.922 --> 12:36.056
Watch out!

12:37.791 --> 12:38.859
What's going on?

12:38.892 --> 12:41.394
(TIRES SCREECH)

12:41.428 --> 12:43.563
Morgan just missed a turn.
She's a terrible driver.

12:43.596 --> 12:45.765
Uh, no, we're on
our way back now.

12:45.799 --> 12:47.600
Hurry.
Okay.

12:47.634 --> 12:49.236
**

12:49.269 --> 12:51.771
(TIRES SCREECH)

12:53.206 --> 12:54.908
(TIRES SCREECH)

13:00.613 --> 13:02.549
How long was I
out in the open?

13:02.582 --> 13:03.884
Thirteen minutes.

13:03.917 --> 13:05.819
We got all of
the infected tissue.

13:05.853 --> 13:07.587
(CELL PHONE DINGS)
That's annoying.

13:07.620 --> 13:10.723
It was necessary
to save your life.

13:10.757 --> 13:12.092
No, I meant
your phone.

13:12.125 --> 13:13.393
Oh. It is.

13:13.426 --> 13:14.962
I bet
it's your girlfriend.

13:16.897 --> 13:18.098
How did you know?

13:19.099 --> 13:21.768
Only annoying girlfriends
text that much.

13:21.801 --> 13:24.237
I used to text
my boyfriend
all the time.

13:24.271 --> 13:25.438
It annoyed him, too.

13:27.507 --> 13:30.810
I am supposed to
flirt with her,

13:30.844 --> 13:32.345
and I don't know how.

13:33.313 --> 13:34.747
Did your boyfriend
break up with you

13:34.781 --> 13:35.983
because
you were annoying?

13:36.016 --> 13:37.184
No. He died.

13:38.785 --> 13:42.155
That's the downside
of outliving your prognosis.

13:42.189 --> 13:44.324
You outlive
everyone else's too.

13:44.357 --> 13:46.126
That is a downside.

13:46.159 --> 13:48.161
(CELL PHONE DINGS)

13:48.195 --> 13:49.429
Get out your phone.

13:49.462 --> 13:51.098
Hmm.

13:51.131 --> 13:52.499
I'll tell you
what to type.

13:52.532 --> 13:54.601
I'm really good
at phone sex.

13:54.634 --> 13:56.970
It's the only
kind of sex
I can have.

13:57.004 --> 13:58.538
We haven't had sex.

13:59.839 --> 14:01.474
I'll stick to foreplay.

14:01.508 --> 14:02.742
No, thank you.

14:02.775 --> 14:06.513
Do you text your parents?
Or are they dead too?

14:06.546 --> 14:07.847
(CHUCKLES)

14:09.516 --> 14:11.518
My parents
are in Denver.

14:13.320 --> 14:15.923
My dad's job
transferred them there.

14:15.956 --> 14:17.891
They always wanted
to live near the snow.

14:20.693 --> 14:25.398
They're outdoorsy,
and I'm, you know, not.

14:27.667 --> 14:31.471
I am not close
to my parents either.

14:31.504 --> 14:33.306
I have autism,
and they don't.

14:35.142 --> 14:37.244
I need to listen
to your lungs.

14:43.250 --> 14:45.485
(SIGHS)
I just got really dizzy.

14:46.653 --> 14:48.088
(SIGHS)

14:49.322 --> 14:50.357
What's going on?

15:02.135 --> 15:03.770
You have an infection.

15:10.077 --> 15:12.845
Temperature is 103.6.
BP is 80/50.

15:12.879 --> 15:14.747
She's showing
early signs of sepsis.

15:14.781 --> 15:16.883
Start her on a course
of IV immunoglobulin therapy,

15:16.916 --> 15:19.352
ADA-enzyme replacement
and GM-CSF.

15:19.386 --> 15:20.653
Okay.

15:20.687 --> 15:22.922
I think we can
do more than
treat her infection...

15:22.956 --> 15:24.891
Gene replacement therapy.

15:24.924 --> 15:27.094
We harvest her stem cells
and use a retroviral vector

15:27.127 --> 15:30.497
to transduce her DNA
with the modified ADA gene.

15:30.530 --> 15:31.831
If it works,
she's cured.

15:31.864 --> 15:33.500
And if it doesn't work,
she dies.

15:33.533 --> 15:36.203
There's a 50% chance
her body will have
an acute toxic reaction.

15:36.236 --> 15:37.404
We're going to treat
the infection.

15:37.437 --> 15:38.838
She'll get
another infection.

15:38.871 --> 15:40.340
And another,
and another,

15:40.373 --> 15:42.375
and eventually,
one of them will
kill her.

15:42.409 --> 15:44.244
You don't know that.
She's already beaten
the odds.

15:44.277 --> 15:46.779
By cutting herself off
from the world.

15:46.813 --> 15:49.116
Traditional treatment
is the safer course.

15:49.149 --> 15:51.618
**

15:53.920 --> 15:55.355
He's blowing off steam.

15:55.388 --> 15:56.823
He's with the doctors.
He's safe.

15:56.856 --> 15:58.758
APRIL: He's scared
and overwhelmed,

15:58.791 --> 16:00.460
and obviously he felt like
he couldn't tell us...

16:00.493 --> 16:03.063
Because you've
been keeping him
under lock and key.

16:03.096 --> 16:04.331
I'm protecting him.

16:07.400 --> 16:08.735
(CRYING)

16:11.038 --> 16:12.705
We have to stay strong.

16:12.739 --> 16:14.874
**

16:14.907 --> 16:16.643
I think Charlie
knows you're strong.

16:17.777 --> 16:19.612
And he knows
you love him.

16:20.747 --> 16:22.382
But the moment you all
heard the word "cancer,"

16:22.415 --> 16:24.584
everything in
Charlie's life changed.

16:25.718 --> 16:28.121
And I think
he needs to know
that, at some point,

16:28.155 --> 16:30.790
it's going to start to feel
like his life again.

16:45.205 --> 16:47.640
My mom and dad used to do
these things called

16:47.674 --> 16:50.243
spontaneous
family adventure days...

16:50.277 --> 16:51.444
SFADs.

16:53.813 --> 16:56.549
They were pretty lame.
But they let me skip school.

16:57.884 --> 17:00.487
Got to go to
baseball games,

17:00.520 --> 17:03.156
drive around
with blaring music.

17:03.190 --> 17:08.061
I got to eat food
that was inorganic
and genetically modified.

17:09.796 --> 17:11.798
Sometimes I even got to
stay up past midnight.

17:17.070 --> 17:19.206
**

17:24.844 --> 17:26.679
Now we go
to doctor's appointments.

17:28.915 --> 17:30.517
And my mom makes lists.

17:31.918 --> 17:33.186
And cries.

17:38.391 --> 17:41.027
And my dad's...quiet.

17:45.865 --> 17:47.200
Just one more
quick stop.

17:47.234 --> 17:49.836
Morgan, Andrews is
expecting us to...

17:49.869 --> 17:52.205
Please,
just 20 more minutes.

17:53.340 --> 17:54.841
Fifteen.

17:54.874 --> 17:57.144
**

18:01.047 --> 18:02.249
(DOOR OPENS)

18:02.282 --> 18:04.584
Park told me you rejected
his gene therapy idea.

18:06.886 --> 18:09.822
We can't dismiss
plausible treatment
options out of fear.

18:09.856 --> 18:11.858
It's not fear.

18:11.891 --> 18:13.526
It's a reasonable
degree of caution.

18:14.594 --> 18:15.862
Since when
are you cautious?

18:17.730 --> 18:21.568
The benefit of the cure
may be worth the risk.

18:21.601 --> 18:22.835
Let Park
take it to her.

18:25.472 --> 18:27.374
No.
It's not worth it.

18:27.407 --> 18:29.276
The cure is riskier
in the short term,

18:29.309 --> 18:31.244
but the long-term upside
is much greater.

18:31.278 --> 18:34.147
We can give you the chance
to live a long, healthy,
normal life.

18:34.814 --> 18:36.983
No, you can't.

18:37.016 --> 18:39.286
I've been a freak
my whole life.

18:39.319 --> 18:42.889
And curing my disease,
letting me take
a breath of fresh air,

18:42.922 --> 18:44.224
it's not gonna
make me normal.

18:44.257 --> 18:45.592
(COUGHS)

18:45.625 --> 18:46.959
Increase the oxygen
to 15 liters.

18:46.993 --> 18:48.295
Start her on the IVIG.

18:50.797 --> 18:53.433
(BEEPING)

18:53.466 --> 18:55.134
We need to
let her rest.

19:01.073 --> 19:03.310
I'm a freak, too.

19:03.343 --> 19:06.145
**

19:06.179 --> 19:07.747
People have
called me that

19:07.780 --> 19:09.916
because I am not
neurotypical.

19:11.684 --> 19:14.287
And I used
to be alone,

19:15.822 --> 19:16.823
like you.

19:19.359 --> 19:21.294
Sometimes
that was easier.

19:21.328 --> 19:25.832
Because it is hard
to be around people

19:25.865 --> 19:27.900
when you're not
like them.

19:27.934 --> 19:31.938
But now
I have Dr. Glassman,

19:31.971 --> 19:33.806
and a roommate
who is a girl,

19:33.840 --> 19:36.709
and a girlfriend who is only
annoying some of the time.

19:36.743 --> 19:40.380
And I think it is better
than being alone.

19:43.983 --> 19:46.753
If you're...cured,

19:46.786 --> 19:50.357
you can be..."outdoorsy"

19:50.390 --> 19:52.425
like your parents.

19:52.459 --> 19:55.127
Or you can stay inside
and have phone sex.

19:58.064 --> 19:59.966
It will be your choice.

19:59.999 --> 20:03.202
**

20:11.711 --> 20:13.646
The next time you go over
my head will be the last.

20:15.748 --> 20:17.183
Prep her for
the gene replacement.

20:21.388 --> 20:22.589
Nice work, Shaun.

20:26.426 --> 20:28.528
No. No way.

20:29.762 --> 20:30.997
He's going blind.

20:31.030 --> 20:33.500
It's his last chance
to see a naked woman.

20:35.067 --> 20:36.703
You're a woman.

20:36.736 --> 20:38.204
I bet under those clothes,
you're a naked one.

20:39.939 --> 20:41.541
I'm his sister.

20:41.574 --> 20:43.343
**

20:44.076 --> 20:45.545
I'll slip you 50 bucks.

20:45.578 --> 20:47.680
(CLICKS TONGUE)

20:47.714 --> 20:49.849
(SIGHS)

20:58.024 --> 21:00.293
My budget proposal,
for your approval.

21:01.260 --> 21:03.696
Surgical cases,
for your review.

21:03.730 --> 21:05.998
Before the board meeting
tomorrow night.

21:06.032 --> 21:07.967
(SIGHS)

21:11.037 --> 21:12.071
The pregnant woman...

21:12.104 --> 21:13.272
(PHONE BEEPS)

21:13.306 --> 21:14.407
How's Neil taking it?

21:14.441 --> 21:16.909
Five minutes, please.
I'm with Dr. Lim.

21:16.943 --> 21:20.079
I see there's a new member
on the clinic team.

21:20.112 --> 21:21.247
How's that going?

21:21.280 --> 21:23.983
Well, it's been half-a-day.
We're working out the kinks.

21:26.419 --> 21:29.422
Well, if it's still
smooth-sailing
by close of business,

21:29.456 --> 21:31.257
let me know
your secret.

21:31.290 --> 21:33.192
I guess that answers
my initial question.

21:33.225 --> 21:35.094
(SIGHS)

21:35.127 --> 21:36.796
He keeps telling me
he's fine.

21:36.829 --> 21:39.165
You're the last person
he'd tell if he weren't.

21:40.500 --> 21:42.201
I'd be the second to last.

21:42.234 --> 21:44.236
(PHONE BEEPS)

21:44.270 --> 21:45.605
I'm almost done.

21:48.641 --> 21:49.742
You're the President.

21:51.177 --> 21:53.913
He has to listen
when you talk.
Or, pretend to.

21:53.946 --> 21:55.448
(DOOR OPENS)

21:55.482 --> 21:58.885
Hey, the four-year-old
with the ear infection
has been here half an hour,

21:58.918 --> 22:01.320
his mother
just pulled out
fingerpaints.

22:01.354 --> 22:02.422
You need to go.

22:02.455 --> 22:03.756
(TAPS DESK)

22:03.790 --> 22:06.793
Debbie, this is Dr. Lim,
Chief of Surgery.

22:06.826 --> 22:09.662
I know.
It's very impressive.

22:09.696 --> 22:12.064
Come back if you get
an ear infection.

22:12.098 --> 22:13.766
**

22:16.503 --> 22:17.670
One more.
No.

22:18.605 --> 22:19.839
We're done.

22:19.872 --> 22:21.408
The surgery can't start
without me.

22:21.441 --> 22:24.544
Where are we going next?
Yosemite? The Great Wall?

22:24.577 --> 22:26.112
The top of Everest?
It's never gonna be enough.

22:26.145 --> 22:27.480
Claire, stop.

22:27.514 --> 22:31.250
You can't pack a lifetime
of things you're gonna miss
into one day.

22:31.283 --> 22:34.621
Your situation sucks,
and it is unfair.

22:34.654 --> 22:37.023
But you know what,
life sucks,
and it's unfair,

22:37.056 --> 22:40.192
and things end
before we're ready.

22:40.226 --> 22:42.328
We are going back.
Now.

22:42.361 --> 22:44.363
**

22:44.397 --> 22:47.767
(CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

22:47.800 --> 22:49.001
(SIGHS)

22:52.038 --> 22:53.039
No.

22:57.810 --> 22:59.011
I'm not gonna
have the surgery.

23:14.494 --> 23:15.895
TARA: How long
before I know

23:15.928 --> 23:18.831
if I've let you talk me
into something really stupid?

23:18.865 --> 23:23.135
You could have
an acute toxic reaction
and die

23:23.169 --> 23:24.571
in the next 24 hours.

23:24.604 --> 23:28.074
But we hope to see
some positive sign
your body is responding soon.

23:31.911 --> 23:33.713
Okay.

23:33.746 --> 23:36.215
Your transfusion is done.
We'll check on you
in a half-hour.

23:37.416 --> 23:38.417
Dr. Murphy.

23:40.653 --> 23:43.590
Would you...
Sit with me?

24:03.042 --> 24:05.111
What do you
want to know?

24:05.978 --> 24:08.848
Nothing. I...

24:08.881 --> 24:10.883
I just want someone
to be here.

24:15.588 --> 24:17.056
In case I croak.

24:19.325 --> 24:20.827
Hmm.

24:23.229 --> 24:25.832
It's probably
all your annoying
girlfriend wants, too.

24:27.900 --> 24:29.301
Just to know
you're there.

24:31.804 --> 24:35.141
Carly's in good health
and unlikely to die soon.

24:37.343 --> 24:39.245
Some girls
have all the luck.

24:45.785 --> 24:46.919
(BEEPING)

24:50.289 --> 24:51.323
Debbie!

24:54.360 --> 24:55.494
You bellowed?

24:55.528 --> 24:56.929
This thing is broken.

24:56.963 --> 24:59.165
Can you call someone from I.T.
and send them over, please?

24:59.198 --> 25:02.434
Oh, I meant to tell you
that I, um, upgraded
our software.

25:02.468 --> 25:04.303
It's gonna be faster,
more efficient.

25:04.336 --> 25:06.205
Not if I don't know
how to use it.

25:06.238 --> 25:09.475
You can't just change
my entire software system
without asking me.

25:09.508 --> 25:11.310
I didn't change it.
I upgraded it.

25:11.343 --> 25:12.444
(BEEP)
There.

25:12.478 --> 25:14.080
Or kick out
my Chief of Surgery.

25:14.113 --> 25:16.616
Or interrupt
my appointments.

25:16.649 --> 25:18.184
You'll be here
20 hours a day

25:18.217 --> 25:19.852
if you don't stick
to a schedule.

25:19.886 --> 25:21.353
It's my call.

25:21.387 --> 25:23.255
I'm not here
to slap on Band-Aids

25:23.289 --> 25:25.291
or to write
prescriptions.

25:25.324 --> 25:27.960
That woman had serious issues
we needed to discuss.

25:27.994 --> 25:30.262
The one with the rodent
in her purse?

25:30.296 --> 25:32.799
It's a squirrel.
It's a Northern
flying squirrel.

25:32.832 --> 25:34.601
You weren't gonna fix
whatever issues she has

25:34.634 --> 25:35.668
with an extra
five minutes.

25:35.702 --> 25:38.805
It's my clinic, okay?
I decide how it runs!

25:41.874 --> 25:43.142
Okay.

25:44.811 --> 25:47.379
I thought that
you wanted me
to be a part of it.

25:47.413 --> 25:49.682
You know,
to actually help
and to...

25:51.317 --> 25:52.985
Make changes,
have opinions.

25:53.019 --> 25:56.155
But if that's not
what you want,
then I...

25:56.188 --> 25:57.657
I should do
what I promised...

25:59.158 --> 26:00.459
I quit.

26:00.492 --> 26:03.229
**

26:05.765 --> 26:07.199
You're out of sutures.

26:24.617 --> 26:25.718
I'm sorry.

26:27.386 --> 26:29.856
I... I shouldn't
have said any of that.

26:34.526 --> 26:36.729
I lost somebody recently.

26:40.199 --> 26:42.068
And it hurts.

26:42.101 --> 26:43.602
A lot.

26:44.871 --> 26:48.775
And I took it out on you,
and that is unfair.

26:54.080 --> 26:56.148
But if you don't
have this surgery,

26:57.784 --> 27:02.755
you won't ever drink
another slushy
at a baseball game.

27:02.789 --> 27:06.558
Or feel the wind in your hair
when you speed down the road.

27:06.592 --> 27:07.727
Or...

27:09.395 --> 27:11.030
Or touch a naked woman.

27:11.063 --> 27:13.265
**

27:16.903 --> 27:17.937
Now, this sucks.

27:17.970 --> 27:19.471
It really, really sucks.

27:20.572 --> 27:23.409
But it will get
less sucky.

27:27.613 --> 27:29.749
And the part
that hurts
so much right now

27:29.782 --> 27:32.618
will start
to hurt less.

27:36.555 --> 27:37.957
And life goes on,

27:37.990 --> 27:39.959
and you will have
wonderful moments,

27:39.992 --> 27:41.828
and you will have
sucky moments.

27:43.162 --> 27:44.764
And it will be
your life.

27:45.832 --> 27:47.934
And it'll be a good life,
Charlie.

27:50.336 --> 27:52.772
I suspect it might
even be a great life.

27:52.805 --> 27:55.474
**

28:03.750 --> 28:05.852
Oh, thank God.
(WHIMPERS)

28:05.885 --> 28:07.019
DR. REZNICK:
Sorry it took a while.

28:08.154 --> 28:09.188
Car trouble.

28:11.991 --> 28:13.459
DR. ANDREWS:
Welcome back, Charlie.

28:13.492 --> 28:14.794
You had
some good people
very worried.

28:15.561 --> 28:17.263
I'm really sorry.

28:17.296 --> 28:20.132
You guys can
ground me forever
for this, but I just...

28:20.166 --> 28:22.168
I just wanted to have
one last day of fun.

28:24.370 --> 28:26.839
We can be fun, too.
Again.

28:29.208 --> 28:31.010
I was thinking

28:31.043 --> 28:33.813
it might be time
to reintroduce the SFADs.

28:33.846 --> 28:38.017
Baseball games, concerts,
staying up late.

28:38.050 --> 28:39.551
That sounds pretty lame.

28:39.585 --> 28:41.020
(LAUGHS)

28:43.189 --> 28:44.824
We're running
a little late,

28:44.857 --> 28:46.158
and we need to
get you prepped.

28:46.192 --> 28:48.594
**

28:52.598 --> 28:55.534
I'm sorry. I need
some 5-0 nylon sutures.

28:57.503 --> 28:59.872
And apparently
we need to talk.

29:01.340 --> 29:04.576
You can report back
to the Chief of Surgery
that I'm fine.

29:04.610 --> 29:05.878
(BEEP)

29:05.912 --> 29:08.915
(INDISTINCT TALKING OVER P.A.)

29:11.083 --> 29:13.319
You don't have to talk to me.
You don't have to talk to her.

29:13.352 --> 29:15.387
But you need to talk
to someone.

29:15.421 --> 29:18.157
I'm not a med student, Aaron.
I've lost patients before.

29:18.190 --> 29:20.692
But you never lost someone
who should have lived.

29:20.726 --> 29:22.929
No one would be fine.
I wouldn't be.

29:22.962 --> 29:24.196
You're not fine.

29:24.230 --> 29:27.433
If for no other reason
than your boss doesn't
think so.

29:27.466 --> 29:28.634
And the bigger problem

29:28.667 --> 29:30.837
is your girlfriend
agrees with her.

29:30.870 --> 29:33.472
**

29:53.725 --> 29:56.062
We'll be right there
as soon as you wake up.

29:56.095 --> 29:59.065
**

30:19.986 --> 30:21.988
We love you so much.

30:23.489 --> 30:24.756
I love you, too.

30:31.630 --> 30:33.132
(SNIFFLES)

30:44.977 --> 30:46.578
We'll take
good care of him.

30:46.612 --> 30:47.679
APRIL: Thank you.

30:55.988 --> 30:58.224
(SNIFFLES)

30:59.325 --> 31:00.326
You ready?

31:06.032 --> 31:07.166
Yeah.

31:10.702 --> 31:12.204
(SIGHS)

31:16.375 --> 31:17.709
I forgot
to take his vitals.

31:19.178 --> 31:20.646
I'm sorry.

31:20.679 --> 31:22.081
Go ahead, I'll...
I'll bring him out.

31:24.516 --> 31:26.385
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

31:33.725 --> 31:35.394
I-I thought
you already took my...

31:35.427 --> 31:37.863
Shut up.

31:39.331 --> 31:40.566
(GASPS)

31:40.599 --> 31:43.535
**

31:43.569 --> 31:45.804
We're bringing
the patient down now.
Vitals okay?

31:45.837 --> 31:48.207
Temp might be a little up,
but he's ready now.

31:53.445 --> 31:55.847
(MONITOR BEEPING)

32:00.186 --> 32:02.321
I just need you
to count back from 10.

32:02.354 --> 32:05.224
Ten...

32:05.257 --> 32:07.226
Nine...

32:07.259 --> 32:09.228
Eight...

32:09.261 --> 32:11.863
Seven...

32:11.897 --> 32:14.666
Six...

32:14.700 --> 32:16.402
Five...

32:16.435 --> 32:19.038
**

32:27.813 --> 32:29.715
(DOOR CLOSES)

32:34.820 --> 32:36.088
You were right.

32:37.656 --> 32:38.991
I'm not fine.

32:41.460 --> 32:42.928
It's okay
not to be fine.

32:50.236 --> 32:51.803
You can't blame yourself.

32:51.837 --> 32:53.139
I was the one
holding the knife.

32:53.172 --> 32:54.606
The blame lies with me.

32:59.478 --> 33:02.648
But the responsibility
is ours.

33:05.351 --> 33:07.919
Yours and...mine?

33:07.953 --> 33:10.189
Yes.

33:10.222 --> 33:12.991
You're not objective
about me

33:13.025 --> 33:14.293
because of
our relationship.

33:15.361 --> 33:16.528
If we weren't together,

33:16.562 --> 33:18.664
I'm not sure
you would've agreed
to let me do that surgery.

33:22.701 --> 33:25.537
You honestly believe
I approved a procedure

33:25.571 --> 33:26.672
that I didn't think
you could do

33:26.705 --> 33:28.307
because we're
sleeping together?

33:28.340 --> 33:30.976
No. You thought
I could do it.

33:31.009 --> 33:32.044
That's the problem.

33:34.713 --> 33:37.616
I think
your personal feelings

33:37.649 --> 33:39.918
may have led you
to overestimate me.

33:39.951 --> 33:43.021
**

33:43.055 --> 33:44.623
You came to me.

33:46.158 --> 33:48.360
You sold me the surgery,

33:48.394 --> 33:50.196
told me that
you could pull it off.

33:50.229 --> 33:54.600
And now I'm at fault
because I believed
that you...

33:54.633 --> 33:55.701
It's not about fault.

33:56.668 --> 33:58.104
It's about being aware

33:58.137 --> 33:59.971
so that this doesn't
happen again.
(SCOFFS)

34:00.005 --> 34:02.441
It will happen again.

34:02.474 --> 34:06.478
I will make decisions.
You will have bad outcomes.

34:08.013 --> 34:10.316
That doesn't mean
either of us was wrong.

34:12.118 --> 34:15.087
My approval
had nothing to do
with our relationship.

34:17.423 --> 34:19.091
We can't know that
for sure.

34:21.560 --> 34:24.330
If we weren't dating,
that woman
might still be alive.

34:27.099 --> 34:29.067
And we both have
to live with that.

34:29.101 --> 34:31.737
**

34:36.942 --> 34:38.344
CHARLIE: Mom?

34:38.377 --> 34:39.911
Dad?

34:39.945 --> 34:41.046
APRIL: We're here, honey.

34:41.079 --> 34:42.181
ENNIS: We're right here.

34:44.550 --> 34:46.818
You did so good.

34:46.852 --> 34:48.220
We're so proud
of you, buddy.

34:49.521 --> 34:51.190
DR. REZNICK: Charlie.

34:51.223 --> 34:53.525
It's Dr. Reznick.
How are you feeling?

34:55.427 --> 34:56.595
Not awesome.

34:59.064 --> 35:00.466
Are you in any pain?

35:01.367 --> 35:02.534
No.

35:02.568 --> 35:03.769
No, I'm okay.

35:06.172 --> 35:07.506
I'll let you rest.

35:09.074 --> 35:10.108
Wait, Dr. Reznick.

35:11.277 --> 35:12.611
Yes?

35:13.812 --> 35:15.781
Thank you so much.

35:15.814 --> 35:17.249
For everything.

35:18.650 --> 35:19.785
You're welcome.

35:21.387 --> 35:22.788
And Dr. Browne?

35:25.391 --> 35:26.758
Dr. Browne,
are you here?

35:26.792 --> 35:28.960
**

35:28.994 --> 35:30.429
DR. MELENDEZ:
Your T-cell count
has increased.

35:30.462 --> 35:32.264
And your fever
dropped to 99.3.

35:32.298 --> 35:33.599
Your body's fighting
the infection.

35:33.632 --> 35:36.034
So, what does that mean?
I'm cured?

35:36.067 --> 35:38.036
It's too early
to use that word exactly.

35:38.069 --> 35:39.371
We'll need to keep you
in isolation

35:39.405 --> 35:40.706
for a few more weeks
to make sure

35:40.739 --> 35:42.541
that your immune system
is developing on pace.

35:44.310 --> 35:48.347
And there is still
a 5% to 7% chance
of a toxic reaction.

35:49.281 --> 35:52.150
But yes, the cure
appears to be working.

35:53.151 --> 35:54.720
You should
tell your parents
the good news.

35:54.753 --> 35:57.723
What are they gonna do?
Feed me juice through a straw?

35:59.225 --> 36:01.960
They could just be here.

36:04.963 --> 36:06.232
I'm fine.

36:07.899 --> 36:09.435
Let us know
if you need anything.

36:09.468 --> 36:10.836
I'll check in on you
in the morning.

36:15.006 --> 36:16.007
Thank you.

36:18.210 --> 36:19.511
For not killing me.

36:21.380 --> 36:22.448
You're welcome.

36:22.481 --> 36:25.517
Oh, there is still
a 5% to 7% chance of a...

36:25.551 --> 36:27.619
Shaun. She knows.

36:28.554 --> 36:31.323
**

36:37.563 --> 36:39.197
(DOOR SLIDES OPEN)

36:43.535 --> 36:47.706
* Even your going

36:49.508 --> 36:52.978
* Let it

36:54.546 --> 37:00.218
* Knows you

37:01.720 --> 37:05.156
